Seventeen people sustained injuries after a taxi and a car collided at the intersection of Umgeni Road and Goble Road on Monday.On arrival Rescue Care Paramedics found the badly damaged taxi had collided with a robot after the initial collision with a car.Arrive Alive spokesperson Thato Mosena said paramedics found that seventeen patients had sustained injuries ranging from minor to serious.&#8220;Three patients had sustained serious injuries to the remaining passengers sustaining moderate injuries&#8221;, said Mosena.All patients were stabilised and transported to various Durban Hospitals for the further care that they required.The exact cause of the collision is unknown.&nbsp;-TNA Reporter